   Lyric clouds, genre maps and distinctive words 

   Wednesday, 22 June 2011 

   
    by  andrew 

     filed under  Trends and Data 
     Comments:  20 

   

   
    	 One of the interesting things that sets even superficially similiar genres of music apart is their lyrical content. Last.fm tags can overlap to a great degree, but we were interested to see what the words can tell you about the subtler shades of meaning that go along with those tags. As usual around here,